<TITLE> BNP to give EC decision Tuesday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept (bdnews24.com)  The BNP will announce its decision on dialogue with the Election Commission after a meeting with its allies on Tuesday, a senior BNP leader said on Sunday. "Secretaries general of all four parties will meet on Sept 16 at the BNP headquarters in Naya Paltan. They will discuss various issues including the dialogue," BNP office secretary Rizvi Ahmed told bdnews24.com. Earlier in the day, chief election commissioner ATM Shamsul Huda said the talks with the BNP might take place any time soon. "We are looking forward to hearing from the BNP," he said. Mianstream BNP leaders have so far skipped talks with the EC. Its two key alliesJamaat-e-Islami and Islami Oikya Jotedid not attend the latest round of dialogue although they had attended the previous rounds. After the Representation of the People Order (Amendment) Ordinance 2008 was passed on Aug 19, the EC invited parties including BNP to the third round talks on the ordinance. The party refused to attend while party chief Khaleda Zia was still behind bars. On Sept 7, chief election commissioner ATM Shamsul Huda said it would not conclude the dialogue process without sitting with BNP. Election commissioner M Sakhawat Hussain said on Sunday the CEC had briefed chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed over the latest round of talks with political parties. He added that talks with the BNP might take place this week. On her release from sepcial jail on Sept 11, BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia announced her intention to attend the dialogue and take part in the national polls. Four caretaker government advisers met her the following day. bdnews
